<event name="RAD_LAB_QUEST_1">
	<text>"Most excellent, to begin with, understand that alot of this is highly advanced, try to keep it underwraps."
	Goose walks you over to a terminal on the wall.
	"Our current issue revolves this station design here," The scientist says, gesturing to the strange looking station design on the terminals screen.
	"As you can see, we've equiped this station with a prototype jump drive, allowing us to move it between systems, it's not agile, but it works. Anyway, on a recent test drive, it was captured by pirates, well a pirate, and due to our overconfidence in the station defences we have no way of tracking it down."
	</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Seems bleak, what do you want us to do?</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Ah, well luckily we've actually managed to track down the pirates who stole our station, unfortunetly we don't know where they've put it."
			The scientist transmits you some cooridinates.
			"What we need is for you to go find them, and attack them, but DON'T KILL THEM, just damage them enough that they try to jump away, and when they do, follow them, we'll give you a device that you can use to follow them when they jump away."
			"Oh, and once you find the station we'll come and meet you with the payment, good hunting."</text>
			<augment name="RAD_JUMP_TRACKER"/>
			<quest event="RAD_PIRATE_TRACKING_1"/>
			<store>STORE_RADLAB</store>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

